            <thetext>When a right-click context menu is assigned to a control, the context menu will disappear as soon as it has appeared if the theme has no border width for the menu.  This is because the qx.ui.menu.Button._onMouseUp() always calls qx.ui.menu.Manager.getInstance().hideAll(), irrespective of whether the button saw a corresponding &quot;mousedown&quot; event.

This problem occurs with the Aristo contrib theme, and a workaround is to add &quot;width:1&quot; to Aristo&#39;s Decoration.js &quot;menu&quot; decorator.</thetext>
